        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "gcU7x",
          "name": "ArticleHeroImage",
          "clip": true,
          "width": "fill_container",
          "height": 480,
          "fill": {
            "type": "image",
            "enabled": true,
            "url": "./images/generated-1771447566052.png",
            "mode": "fill"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "0IMFK",
          "name": "ArticleBody",
          "width": "fill_container",
          "layout": "vertical",
          "gap": 32,
          "padding": [
            64,
            300
          ],
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "m21r7",
              "fill": "#FFFFFF",
              "content": "The Agile Promise vs Reality",
              "fontFamily": "Instrument Serif",
              "fontSize": 28,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "DASgE",
              "fill": "#ADADB0",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "Organizations worldwide have embraced agile methodologies with the promise of faster delivery, better quality, and happier teams. Yet study after study shows that a significant percentage of agile transformations fail to achieve their goals. After leading transformations across five different organizations over the past eight years, I've observed consistent patterns that separate successful adoptions from expensive failures.",
              "lineHeight": 1.8,
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 16,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "Fniod",
              "fill": "#ADADB0",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "The problem isn't agile itself — it's how organizations approach the transformation. Too often, companies treat agile as a process change rather than a cultural shift. They hire Scrum Masters, set up Jira boards, and schedule daily standups, then wonder why nothing has fundamentally changed.",
              "lineHeight": 1.8,
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 16,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "2UK2n",
              "name": "QuoteBlock",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "stroke": {
                "thickness": {
                  "left": 3
                },
                "fill": "#D4AF37"
              },
              "layout": "vertical",
              "gap": 12,
              "padding": [
                0,
                0,
                0,
                24
              ],
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "uEzEK",
                  "fill": "#FFFFFF",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "\"Agile is not a methodology. It's a mindset. You can't install a mindset — you have to grow one.\"",
                  "lineHeight": 1.5,
                  "fontFamily": "Instrument Serif",
                  "fontSize": 20,
                  "fontWeight": "normal",
                  "fontStyle": "italic"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "icQzM",
                  "fill": "#D4AF37",
                  "content": "— Jeff Sutherland, Co-creator of Scrum",
                  "fontFamily": "DM Mono",
                  "fontSize": 13,
                  "fontWeight": "500"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "2EJXc",
              "fill": "#FFFFFF",
              "content": "The Three Pillars of Successful Transformation",
              "fontFamily": "Instrument Serif",
              "fontSize": 28,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "ZZb6x",
              "fill": "#ADADB0",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "Through my experience, I've identified three critical pillars that must be in place for an agile transformation to succeed. Missing even one of these creates significant risk of failure.",
              "lineHeight": 1.8,
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 16,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "qpeer",
              "name": "Pillar1",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "gap": 16,
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "sdSyy",
                  "name": "p1Num",
                  "width": 36,
                  "height": 36,
                  "fill": "#D4AF3718",
                  "cornerRadius": 18,
                  "justifyContent": "center",
                  "alignItems": "center",
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "TBpyw",
                      "fill": "#D4AF37",
                      "content": "1",
                      "fontFamily": "DM Mono",
                      "fontSize": 16,
                      "fontWeight": "600"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "OmGv0",
                  "name": "p1Content",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "layout": "vertical",
                  "gap": 8,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "ZU1n8",
                      "fill": "#FFFFFF",
                      "content": "Executive Sponsorship & Alignment",
                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                      "fontSize": 18,
                      "fontWeight": "600"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "7TQ0Q",
                      "fill": "#ADADB0",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "Leadership must understand that agile is not just for the development team. It requires organizational changes to budgeting, governance, and decision-making processes. Without genuine executive buy-in, transformation efforts will hit a ceiling.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.8,
                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                      "fontSize": 16,
                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "2EqPa",
              "name": "Pillar2",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "gap": 16,
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "6XrjQ",
                  "name": "p2Num",
                  "width": 36,
                  "height": 36,
                  "fill": "#D4AF3718",
                  "cornerRadius": 18,
                  "justifyContent": "center",
                  "alignItems": "center",
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "Guc6Z",
                      "fill": "#D4AF37",
                      "content": "2",
                      "fontFamily": "DM Mono",
                      "fontSize": 16,
                      "fontWeight": "600"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "T8WOQ",
                  "name": "p2Content",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "layout": "vertical",
                  "gap": 8,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "aze8J",
                      "fill": "#FFFFFF",
                      "content": "Team Empowerment & Psychological Safety",
                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                      "fontSize": 18,
                      "fontWeight": "600"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "Gf59A",
                      "fill": "#ADADB0",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "Teams need to feel safe to experiment, fail, and learn. If your retrospectives are performative or team members fear speaking up, you've built the structure without the foundation. Invest in creating environments where honest feedback is valued.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.8,
                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                      "fontSize": 16,
                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "Y8Oy6",
              "name": "Pillar3",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "gap": 16,
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "eIC4x",
                  "name": "p3Num",
                  "width": 36,
                  "height": 36,
                  "fill": "#D4AF3718",
                  "cornerRadius": 18,
                  "justifyContent": "center",
                  "alignItems": "center",
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "UTmzd",
                      "fill": "#D4AF37",
                      "content": "3",
                      "fontFamily": "DM Mono",
                      "fontSize": 16,
                      "fontWeight": "600"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "u69sk",
                  "name": "p3Content",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "layout": "vertical",
                  "gap": 8,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "6Q3DS",
                      "fill": "#FFFFFF",
                      "content": "Continuous Improvement Over Perfection",
                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                      "fontSize": 18,
                      "fontWeight": "600"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "Vshxj",
                      "fill": "#ADADB0",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "The goal isn't to implement the perfect agile framework on day one. It's to create a culture of continuous improvement where processes evolve based on real feedback. Start small, measure outcomes, and iterate — just like you would with a product.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.8,
                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                      "fontSize": 16,
                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "line",
              "id": "QPLki",
              "fill": "#1F1F23",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "height": 1
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "dFROm",
              "fill": "#FFFFFF",
              "content": "Moving Forward",
              "fontFamily": "Instrument Serif",
              "fontSize": 28,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "hrcp8",
              "fill": "#ADADB0",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "Agile transformation is a journey, not a destination. The organizations that succeed are the ones that commit to the long game — investing in people, creating safe spaces for experimentation, and measuring success by outcomes rather than output. If your transformation has stalled, revisit these three pillars and ask yourself honestly: are they truly in place?",
              "lineHeight": 1.8,
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 16,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            }
          ]
        },
